The paper addresses the problem of 3D human pose estimation from a sequence of 2D human poses using deep learning techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of LSTM units and temporal smoothness constraint, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The problem of 3D pose estimation can also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
